# zcf --> zip and compress it into a file
# Here the zipped and compressed file is backup.tar.gz
# C --> Change the Directory
# /var/ is the Directory and inside the /var/ log is the main folder that we're trying to zip and compress
# x --> Extract
# v --> Verbose (Show the result)

==============================================================================================================

# Creating a zipped and compressed file using tar

tar -zcf backup.tar.gz -C /var/ log

# Extracting the tar file using -x
# since we zipped and compressed log folder to backup.tar.gz,
# While we extract backup.tar.gz again --> log folder will be created in the current directory

tar -xzvf backup.tar.gz

==============================================================================================================